text: Waldenbuch is a town in Böblingen in Baden-Württemberg, Germany. It is known for its chocolate brand Ritter Sport. == Geography == Waldenbuch is at an elevation reaching from 340 to 460 meters on the northern edge of Schönbuch forest. It is 16 km south of Stuttgart. === Districts === Waldenbuch has following districts of Sonnenhang, Kalkofen, Weilerberg, Glashütte, Stadtkern ("Städtle"), Liebenau and Hasenhof. == References == == Other websites == * Official website Category:Böblingen (district)
